The paper presents a novel algorithm for L1-norm principal component analysis, which is a common technique in machine learning and data analysis. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the algorithm and compares it to other known algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves numerical optimization and matrix computations, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Systems and Control).
